This readme describes the steps needed to test the AGW without OpenFlow

On gateway VM,
- Install the kernel GTP module, libgtpnl library and nating rule:
  `sudo bash $MAGMA_ROOT/lte/gateway/deploy/roles/magma/files/setup_gw2_gtp.sh`

- Once the above script succeeds, `modinfo gtp` should show
  `/lib/modules/4.9.0-9-amd64/kernel/drivers/net/gtp.ko` as the module filename

- Build the AGW without OpenFlow support,
  cd $MAGMA_ROOT/lte/gateway
  make FEATURES=agw_gtpnl run

- (Optional) For debugging, enable debug logging for gtp kernel module
	sudo su;
  echo 'module gtp +p' > /sys/kernel/debug/dynamic_debug/control
  tail -f /var/log/kern.log

On test VM,
- Remove the ovs test case from the list of tests run as part of integ_test
  `sudo bash
$MAGMA_ROOT/lte/gateway/deploy/roles/magma_test/files/setup_gw2_s1tests.sh`
